  "text": "Low spatial and high temporal frequencies in luminance contrast profiles are related to the Magnocellular function. On the other hand, high spatial and low temporal frequencies are related to Parvocellular function [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The different stimulus sizes used in our protocol showed to be selective for the Magnocellular and Parvocellular contribution to contrast sensitivity. A detailed account of MC and PC selectivity is presented in the following sections.",
